@danny.lan `aihub-extraction.spec.ts` failed in this Cypress run (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/15221/overview/2ccf5f7b-8023-4ee1-9804-6c7b8baa378f/replay?roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1730233401932.9&att=1) because it's trying to click the "document reasoning" option (based this PR (https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/58143)) but now we also have the "visual reasoning" option. It passed in this Cypress run where it updates the feature flag to IB_OPT_IN. It passed because the feature flag mocking didn't work because we named the feature flag incorrectly in `env-local-featurel-flags.json` `aihub_enable_visual_reasoning` instead of `aihub_enable_vision_reasoning`

https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/64271
